elements.2211.03206_bbe3fb646a2821c53ec2e4299a5b2: The edge bisection problem, or more general the edge isoperimetric problem, has been intensively studied in the literature and has a wide range of applications
elements.2211.03206_3e9d6da2e7fca43b09c2bf432efb6: One of the reasons is that there are available tools, from randomized algorithms to spectral techniques, which make the problem more approachable than its related vertex bisection problem, or the more general vertex isoperimetric problem
elements.2211.03206_340c702ad036931668ca2231ddc46: For constant degree, most of the applications to computer science and other areas, bounds on edge isoperimetry are usually enough even if vertex isoperimetry is concerned
elements.2211.03206_ebe468aac1395e2c378c482972869: However, from the theoretical point of view, it is a natural and important question to understand the behaviour of the two parameters
elements.2211.03206_829d5f0aceda414a52fdf1b4655a2: The vertex isoperimetric problem is solved for a few classes of graphs
elements.2211.03206_039b5c68a184db5d35984bed57c14: A particularly significant one is the solutions by Harper
elements.2211.03206_ed9c948c86127ea8a1c58d5706603: for the vertex and edge isoperimetric problems on the hypercube
elements.2211.03206_b3e5bcce7188f758a8d6b92c66210: Interestingly, the minimizers for both problems in the hypercube are structurally very different
elements.2211.03206_1014f16f213a7ee0cf634bd8723db: This prompted us to investigate the vertex bisection problem for random regular graphs
elements.2211.03206_2c5a9e2818e8901fadcef792c1bbe: For fixed small degree, the best bounds for the edge vertex bisection of random regular graphs have been obtained by Diaz, Serna and Wormald
elements.2211.03206_dfc035fe355415676bf326c2f492d: by analyzing a greedy algorithm with the differential equations method
elements.2211.03206_faa9574d7ea51cc78b2477be5d9fc: does not provide good vertex bisectors, indicating that the minimizing bisectors for the case of edge cuts and vertex cuts have distinct structural properties
elements.2211.03206_cb48f41256ebb2c7c9ff88232ebc8: In this paper we consider a different randomized greedy algorithm to obtain upper bounds on the vertex bisection width of random regular graphs, which is also analyzed with the differential equation method
elements.2211.03206_1872c3b42843237f28e50915e7010: The results are compared with the lower bounds for this parameter obtained by Kolesnik and Wormald
elements.2211.03206_ac62efbf1aae2d4323159d01fb77c: and also with experimental results with a simplified version of the randomized greedy algorithm
elements.2211.03206_a818be99bfb9ad0dbefb4d49015ad: To the best of our knowledge our algorithm provides the first upper bounds for the vertex bisection problem of random regular graphs
elements.2211.03206_6e7fbf89aaec883101b3c0d9112ca: The gaps between lower and upper bounds certainly leave room for improvement, which is the more relevant natural question left open.
